docs.abstract: An arbitrator determined that the quarterback’s lawyers had unearthed sufficient evidence of collusion by N.F.L. owners to keep the free-agent quarterback off the field.
docs.snippet: An arbitrator determined that the quarterback’s lawyers had unearthed sufficient evidence of collusion by N.F.L. owners to keep the free-agent quarterback off the field.
docs.lead_paragraph: In a major blow to the N.F.L., Colin Kaepernick achieved a preliminary but important win in his case accusing the league of colluding to keep him off the field because of the player protests during the national anthem that he instigated.

headline.main: Colin Kaepernick’s Collusion Case Against the N.F.L. Will Advance
headline.print_headline: Kaepernick May Proceed With Case, Ruling Says

docs.abstract: Despite a ruling from the arbitrator allowing the case to continue, the N.F.L. is not inclined to settle. Neither is Kaepernick.
docs.snippet: Despite a ruling from the arbitrator allowing the case to continue, the N.F.L. is not inclined to settle. Neither is Kaepernick.
docs.lead_paragraph: Proving that a team or a league colluded to keep a player off the field has been difficult over the years.

headline.main: Colin Kaepernick Is Not Going Away
headline.print_headline: Why the N.F.L. And Kaepernick Haven’t Settled

docs.abstract: Top executives have long been enlisted, to very good effect, to star in commercials for their companies. But it can be a fraught strategy, as the troubles at Papa John’s have shown.
docs.snippet: Top executives have long been enlisted, to very good effect, to star in commercials for their companies. But it can be a fraught strategy, as the troubles at Papa John’s have shown.
docs.lead_paragraph: Commercials for Dollar Shave Club, the subscription toiletries company, are known for two things. There’s that zany, slightly frat-boy sense of humor — the latest ad features a few dozen people shaving, tweezing, clipping, trimming, waxing, bathing, powdering, spritzing, gelling, styling and moisturizing to the song “I’ve Gotta Be Me” as crooned by Steve Lawrence.

headline.main: Warts and All? That’s the Risk When a Founder Is the Face of a Company
headline.print_headline: When the Founder Is the Face of the Company

docs.abstract: ESPN’s president said the N.F.L. did not pressure the network to make the change, even amid continuing criticism of players who use the anthem to protest social injustice.
docs.snippet: ESPN’s president said the N.F.L. did not pressure the network to make the change, even amid continuing criticism of players who use the anthem to protest social injustice.
docs.lead_paragraph: ESPN said on Friday that it would not show the national anthem before the “Monday Night Football” games it broadcasts this season, even as the debate over player protests continues.

headline.main: ESPN Won’t Show National Anthem Before Monday Night Football Games
headline.print_headline: ESPN Won’t Show Anthem at Monday Games

docs.abstract: The novelist’s only children’s book is coming back into print, and it couldn’t be more timely.
docs.snippet: The novelist’s only children’s book is coming back into print, and it couldn’t be more timely.
docs.lead_paragraph: “I never had a childhood,” the writer James Baldwin once said. “I was born dead.”

headline.main: A James Baldwin Book, Forgotten and Overlooked for Four Decades, Gets Another Life
headline.print_headline: Baldwin’s ‘Little Man’ Grows Into Its Time

docs.abstract: Malcolm Jenkins was one of several players who protested before Thursday’s preseason games. Two players who knelt drew praise from Colin Kaepernick.
docs.snippet: Malcolm Jenkins was one of several players who protested before Thursday’s preseason games. Two players who knelt drew praise from Colin Kaepernick.
docs.lead_paragraph: The morning after a handful of N.F.L. players renewed their protests against social inequality and police brutality by raising fists or kneeling during the playing of the national anthem, President Trump renewed his criticism of their actions.

headline.main: Trump Blasts N.F.L. Players as Protests Resume During Anthem

byline.original: By Ken Belson and Benjamin Hoffman

docs.abstract: Over 12 years in charge, Ms. Nooyi worked to diversify the company’s products away from decreasingly profitable sugary soft drinks.
docs.snippet: Over 12 years in charge, Ms. Nooyi worked to diversify the company’s products away from decreasingly profitable sugary soft drinks.
docs.lead_paragraph: In her 12 years as chief executive of PepsiCo, Indra K. Nooyi has been part of an elite club: She is one of only a small number of women leading large corporations. It is a position that has often meant her every move received greater scrutiny than the actions of her male peers.

headline.main: Indra Nooyi, PepsiCo C.E.O. Who Pushed for Healthier Products, to Step Down
headline.print_headline: As PepsiCo’s C.E.O. Plans Exit, Women’s Corporate Clout Fades

docs.abstract: On Aug. 28, 1968, violent clashes in Chicago between demonstrators and the police produced one of the most polarizing showdowns of the 1960s. People are still debating what it all meant.
